    "created_at": "2018-12-13T19:53:02Z",
    "updated_at": "2018-12-13T19:53:02Z",
    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "Some more info about this.\r\n\r\nIt should handle these methods: `eth_requestAccounts` from EIP1193, `eth_accounts`, `eth_sendTransaction` and `eth_sign`. `eth_sign` is a mess, let's just return an error explaining that it's not supported.\r\n\r\nWe already depend on `ethereumjs-util`, so let's use `ethereumjs-tx` for this. Signing a transaction requires all of its params. Those are: nonce, gasPrice, gasLimit, to, value, data and chainId.\r\n\r\nYou can use [this RPC call](https://github.com/ethereum/wiki/wiki/JSON-RPC#eth_gettransactioncount) for the nonce. You should probably use `\"pending\"` as second param. chainId could be set in the constructor. And let's just throw if gasPrice or gasLimit is missing, we'll have a better understanding of what to do with them in the future.",
